💬 IIV League, Are y’all good at saying “No” to people? 🥺 It’s taken me YEARS to start even working decent boundaries into my life. And it still stresses me out even with my close friends. 

It’s the dumbest thing but I feel like I’ll be a burden or it’ll be unnecessarily harsh for them to hear so I just never say anything. Cause what if worse case happens and they DONT LIKE ME ANYMORE? Then I’d die. I’d just die. Because that’s the worst thing that can happen to a human. Not being liked. 😌

Happy Friday 👋

🧐Lately, Life has been filled with more uncertainty than I’ve ever experienced. I moved away from family. I’m having to redefine my values with new info in the world that’s different than I thought when I was growing up.

😩In all honesty, being uncertain if I could handle not knowing the answer to heavy questions about life stopped me from genuinely connecting with folks. Mostly cause I’m scared I’ll find despair at the bottom of all the uncertainty. And what can anyone do to fix that on their own?

🦃I realized this when hanging with my family for Thanksgiving. I didn’t wanna “pry” too much into everyone’s personal lives like I used to cause I don’t feel like I have all the answers to support them anymore. Why open a wound you feel like you have no tools to fix??

BUT ☝️maybe just caring enough to ask and listen with our ears and hearts as well as just *being there* through the discomfort of uncertainty that can exist in life is enough? 

Idk though, I’m not a doctor. Keep your heart open and keep being great! Love yall 🙏🤪
